terms.medium_def:
A High Priest living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Sa.1.3; 
only referred to as Eli (עֵלִי); 
father of Hophni, Phinehas. § descendant of Aaron through Ithamar and high priest and judge of Israel when Samuel entered service as a child

A location first mentioned at Num.34.4; 
only referred to as Akrabbim (עַקְרַבִּים). § a pass on the southern border of Palestine
scorpion-pass; ascent of Akrabbim

A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.36.23; 
referred to as Alvan or Alvan (עַלְיָן, עַלְוָן); 
son of Shobal; 
a brother of Manahath, Ebal, Shepho and Onam. § a Horite, son of Shobal
